28#ifndef EVENT2_KEYVALQ_STRUCT_H_INCLUDED_
29#define EVENT2_KEYVALQ_STRUCT_H_INCLUDED_
30
31#ifdef __cplusplus
32extern "C" {
33#endif
34
35/* Fix so that people don't have to run with <sys/queue.h> */
36/* XXXX This code is duplicated with event_struct.h */
37#ifndef TAILQ_ENTRY
38#define EVENT_DEFINED_TQENTRY_
39#define TAILQ_ENTRY(type) \
40struct { \
41 struct type *tqe_next; /* next element */ \
42 struct type **tqe_prev; /* address of previous next element */ \
43}
44#endif /* !TAILQ_ENTRY */
45
46#ifndef TAILQ_HEAD
47#define EVENT_DEFINED_TQHEAD_
48#define TAILQ_HEAD(name, type) \
49struct name { \
50 struct type *tqh_first; \
51 struct type **tqh_last; \
52}
53#endif
54
55/*
56 * Key-Value pairs. Can be used for HTTP headers but also for
57 * query argument parsing.
58 */
59struct evkeyval {
60 TAILQ_ENTRY(evkeyval) next;
61
62 char *key;
63 char *value;
64};
65
66TAILQ_HEAD (evkeyvalq, evkeyval);
67
68/* XXXX This code is duplicated with event_struct.h */
69#ifdef EVENT_DEFINED_TQENTRY_
70#undef TAILQ_ENTRY
71#endif
72
73#ifdef EVENT_DEFINED_TQHEAD_
74#undef TAILQ_HEAD
75#endif
76
77#ifdef __cplusplus
78}
79#endif
80
81#endif
